SWAIN, Respondent, v. THOMPSON et al., Appellants. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 9, 1894.) Appeal from city court, general term. Action by Charles Swain against Denman Thompson and another.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

J. T. Easton, for appellants. A J. Dittenhofer, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs. See 26 N. Y. Supp. 5361
